o trailer and skips condensation → checkpoint branch never advances.\\n\\n### Why cursor-cli breaks this\\n\\n`hasTTY()` (line 45-79) checks:\\n1. `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY` env var — **not set** in cursor's tmux session\\n2. `GEMINI_CLI` env var — not applicable\\n3. `COPILOT_CLI` env var — not applicable\\n4. `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` — not set\\n5. Opens `/dev/tty` — **succeeds** in tmux (tmux provides a PTY)\\n\\nResult: `hasTTY()` = **true** → fast path skipped.\\n\\n### Why other agents aren't affected\\n\\n| Agent | Why `hasTTY()` = false |\\n|-------|----------------------|\\n| Claude Code | Runs headless (`-p` flag, `cmd.Stdin = nil`) → `/dev/tty` fails |\\n| Gemini CLI | Sets `GEMINI_CLI=1` → explicit check returns false |\\n| Copilot CLI | Sets `COPILOT_CLI=1` → explicit check returns false |\\n| OpenCode | Runs headless → no controlling terminal |\\n\\n### Why some cursor-cli tests pass\\n\\nThe failing tests all ask the agent to commit **during its first turn**. The passing tests involving commits either:\\n- Have the **user** commit (via `s.Git(t, \\\"commit\\\", ...)` which sets `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0`)\\n- Have **multiple turns** before the commit — prior turns' Stop hooks save content to the shadow branch, so `filterSessionsWithNewContent` (the fallback path after fast-path is skipped) finds content and adds the trailer\\n\\nFor single-turn-with-commit: no prior Stop hook → no shadow branch content → `filterSessionsWithNewContent` returns empty → no trailer → no checkpoint.\\n\\n### Fix options\\n\\n1. **Add cursor detection to `hasTTY()`** — needs cursor's CLI binary to set an env var (like `CURSOR_CLI=1`), similar to Gemini/Copilot. This is the production-correct fix but requires coordination with Cursor.\\n\\n2. **Remove `!hasTTY()` guard when session is ACTIVE** — always use the fast path for ACTIVE sessions regardless of TTY. Trade-off: humans who commit while an agent is active won't get the confirmation prompt (trailer is auto-added). This seems like reasonable default behavior.\\n\\n3. **Set `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` in cursor E2E tmux session** — quick E2E-only fix, doesn't address production.\\n\\n4. **Set `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"` in E2E settings for cursor** — another E2E-only fix.\\n\\nOption 2 is probably the cleanest: if a session is ACTIVE, the commit is almost certainly from the agent, and the fast path should apply regardless of TTY. Want me to implement one of these fixes?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":5453,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":108222,\"output_tokens\":5462,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":5453,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ7J92se5ZJEr7GXrnJLV\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"12e808db-612b-432f-b5f7-5ba6a69985b2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T19:18:45.614Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"4a93df6c-18f9-424f-af2a-6ee3b41ac6aa\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"vivid-doodling-bird\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"12e808db-612b-432f-b5f7-5ba6a69985b2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"e9227e51-369b-49fe-916f-9ee141f3b4b6\",\"toolUseID\":\"e9227e51-369b-49fe-916f-9ee141f3b4b6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T19:18:45.730Z\",\"uuid\":\"5b429ed6-0801-410b-873f-abf0cb18ac2f\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"4a93df6c-18f9-424f-af2a-6ee3b41ac6aa\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"vivid-doodling-bird\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5b429ed6-0801-410b-873f-abf0cb18ac2f\",\"