2-47a0-b260-183961dd6cb0/87874108-eff2-47a0-b260-183961dd6cb0.jsonl\\n```\\n\\n## Where to fix\\n\\nIn `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`, around line 521:\\n\\n```go\\nliveData, err := os.ReadFile(state.TranscriptPath)\\nif err != nil {\\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to read live transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nWhen `os.ReadFile(state.TranscriptPath)` fails with a file-not-found error, re-resolve the transcript path using the agent's `ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID)` method and retry. The agent can be obtained via `agent.GetByAgentType(state.AgentType)`. The session dir is `filepath.Dir(state.TranscriptPath)` and the agent session ID is `state.SessionID`.\\n\\nCursor's `ResolveSessionFile` already handles both flat and nested layouts (see `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go:75`):\\n```go\\nfunc (c *CursorAgent) ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID string) string {\\n    nestedDir := filepath.Join(sessionDir, agentSessionID)\\n    nested := filepath.Join(nestedDir, agentSessionID+\\\".jsonl\\\")\\n    if _, err := os.Stat(nested); err == nil {\\n        return nested\\n    }\\n    if info, err := os.Stat(nestedDir); err == nil && info.IsDir() {\\n        return nested\\n    }\\n    return filepath.Join(sessionDir, agentSessionID+\\\".jsonl\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## IMPORTANT: Also fix the same pattern in other places\\n\\nThere are **other places** that read from `state.TranscriptPath` and would have the same issue. Check all uses in the strategy package:\\n\\n1. `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript` (line 521) - the main condensation path\\n2. `hasNewTranscriptWork` (around line 1485) - checks if transcript has new content  \\n3. `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` (around line 1545) - extracts modified files\\n4. The finalize path (around line 2164) that reads the transcript\\n\\nFor all these, apply the same fix: when reading from `state.TranscriptPath` fails with not-found, try re-resolving via the agent.\\n\\n## Implementation approach\\n\\nThe cleanest approach is to add a helper function that:\\n1. Tries to read the stored `state.TranscriptPath`\\n2. If it fails with `os.ErrNotExist`, uses the agent's `ResolveSessionFile` to find the correct path\\n3. If the re-resolved path is different and exists, updates `state.TranscriptPath` (so subsequent reads use the correct path) and returns the data\\n4. Otherwise returns the original error\\n\\nSomething like:\\n\\n```go\\n// resolveTranscriptPath attempts to read the transcript at state.TranscriptPath.\\n// If the file doesn't exist, it re-resolves the path using the agent's\\n// ResolveSessionFile method (handles agents that relocate transcripts mid-session,\\n// e.g., Cursor CLI switching from flat to nested layout).\\n// On success, updates state.TranscriptPath to the resolved path.\\nfunc resolveTranscriptPath(state *SessionState) (string, error) {\\n    // ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: `SessionState` is defined in `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` but is used in the strategy package as `session.State` or aliased. Check the actual type usage in the file.\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n1. Write a unit test in the strategy package that simulates the scenario: stored path is flat but file exists at nested path. Verify the function re-resolves correctly.\\n2. Run `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` to verify all tests pass.\\n\\n## What NOT to do\\n- Don't change the cursor agent's `ResolveSessionFile` — it already handles both layouts correctly\\n- Don't change how `before-submit-prompt` stores the path — the agent reports what it reports\\n- Don't add cursor-specific logic to the strategy layer — keep it generic using the agent interface\"}]},\"uuid\":\"1364c91f-ec03-4ec8-9abd-c666bd806d9c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T19:40:22.572Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"## Task\\n\\nFix a bug where Cursor CLI's transcript path chan