re/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"4a93df6c-18f9-424f-af2a-6ee3b41ac6aa\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"vivid-doodling-bird\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4cea5517-5abb-48bd-9430-26051c664446\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T19:55:00.774Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01AEMAs5aW84vFrnnZFWri5L\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012LbUfAbqQ9K9KG9sVoiJpp\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/requirements/cursor-transcript-path-fix/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Summary: Cursor CLI Transcript Path Fix\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nCursor CLI version 2026.03.11 changed its transcript storage layout mid-session. The `before-submit-prompt` hook reports a flat path (`agent-transcripts/<id>.jsonl`), but by the time `post-commit` runs, the file has been relocated to a nested path (`agent-transcripts/<id>/<id>.jsonl`). This caused condensation to fail with a file-not-found error.\\n\\n## What Was Implemented\\n\\n### New Helper: `resolveTranscriptPath`\\n\\nAdded a generic helper function in `resolve_transcript.go` that:\\n1. Checks if `state.TranscriptPath` exists via `os.Stat`\\n2. On `os.ErrNotExist`, uses `agent.GetByAgentType` + `ResolveSessionFile` to find the new path\\n3. If the resolved path differs and exists, updates `state.TranscriptPath` in place\\n4. Returns the resolved path or the original error\\n\\n### Call Sites Updated\\n\\nApplied the helper at all five locations that read from `state.TranscriptPath`:\\n\\n1. **`extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript`** (condensation.go) -- main condensation path; replaces direct `os.ReadFile`\\n2. **`CondenseSession`** (condensation.go) -- resolves before passing to `extractSessionData` and `prepareTranscriptIfNeeded`\\n3. **`hasNewTranscriptWork`** (hooks.go) -- resolves before `GetTranscriptPosition` and `PrepareTranscript`\\n4. **`extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript`** (hooks.go) -- resolves before `ReadFile` and `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`\\n5. **`finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`** (hooks.go) -- resolves before reading full transcript for finalization\\n\\n## Tests Added\\n\\nNew test file `resolve_transcript_test.go` with 7 test cases:\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_FileExists` -- fast path, file at stored location\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_ReResolvesToNestedLayout` -- simulates the Cursor flat-to-nested relocation\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_FileNotFoundAndCannotResolve` -- re-resolution also fails\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_UnknownAgentFallsThrough` -- unknown agent type\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_EmptyPath` -- empty transcript path\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_DirectoryPathReturnsAsIs` -- path is a directory (Stat succeeds)\\n- `TestResolveTranscriptPath_ClaudeCodeNoReResolution` -- generic behavior for Claude Code agent\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n- **Agent-agnostic**: The fix uses the generic `ResolveSessionFile` agent interface method, not Cursor-specific logic. Any agent that relocates transcripts will benefit.\\n- **State mutation**: `resolveTranscriptPath` updates `state.TranscriptPath` on successful resolution so subsequent reads within the same hook invocation use the corrected path without repeating resolution.\\n- **Idempotent**: If the path already resolves correctly, the function returns immediately (cheap `os.Stat` check). Multiple calls are safe.\\n- **Error semantics**: Non-ENOENT errors (permissions, etc.) are returned immediately without attempting re-resolution.\\n\\n## Validation\\n\\n- `mise run fmt` -- clean\\n- `mise run lint` -- 0 issues\\n- `mise run test:ci` -- all tests pass (unit, integration, and 51 E2E canary tests)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":353,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":90760,\"